    Description: Judgement
    Page: 51
By: Marcus Tullius Cicero
---
There are no snares more dangerous than those which lurk under the guise
of duty or the name of relationship. For the man who is your declared
foe you can easily baffle by precaution; but this hidden, intestine,
and domestic danger not merely exists but overwhelms you before you can
foresee and examine it.
